subSubSection.paragraph:
Male gonopore slightly anterior to middle of somite XI c12 (Fig. 
2F
). Female gonopore in somite XIII b2/a2, inconspicuous, located posterior to gastropore (Fig. 
2F, G
). Gonopores separated by 1/2 + 8 annuli (Fig. 
2F
).

Anterior ganglionic mass in somite VI a2 and a3. Ganglion VII in somite VII b2. Ganglia VIII and IX, of each somite, in b2 and a2. Ganglia X and XI, of each somite, in a2 (Fig. 
3B
). Ganglia XII and XIII, of each somite, in b2 and a2 (Fig. 
3B
). Ganglion XIV in somite XIV a2 (Fig. 
3B
). Ganglion XV in somite XV b2 and a2 (Fig. 
3B
). Ganglion XVI in somite XVI a2 (Fig. 
3B
). Ganglia XVII-XXII, of each somite, in b2 and a2 (Fig. 
3B
). Ganglia XXIII and XXIV, of each somite, in a2. Ganglion XXV in somite XXV b2 and a2. Ganglion XXVI in somite XXVI b1 and b2. Posterior ganglionic mass in somite XXVI c11 and c12.

